<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,935,1322]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,1115,1141]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">Remark</emphasis>
. The species was described by 
<specimenCount box="[642,777,1115,1141]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
from “West Tien-mu-shan” and “Ost Tien-mu-shan” which are 
<typeStatus box="[195,297,1151,1177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">syntypes</typeStatus>
. In order to stabilize the nomenclature we hereby designate the female from “West Tien-mu-shan” labeled as “Type” and deposited in ZFMK as 
<typeStatus box="[670,776,1187,1213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The second 
<typeStatus box="[924,1011,1187,1213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">syntype</typeStatus>
female was not located in the ZFMK collection and is probably deposited in Reich’s private collection which is currently stored in the collection of 
<collectingRegion country="Israel" name="Tel Aviv" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">Tel Aviv</collectingRegion>
University (
<collectingCountry box="[345,412,1259,1285]" name="Israel" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">Israel</collectingCountry>
), or lost. The male of the species is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
